description.p:
A fifteenth of the present invention provides a method for preparing 3'-PEG-CPG the method including:
1) reacting CPG with 3-aminopropyltriethoxysilane to form long chain alkyl amine controlled pore glass (LCAA-CPG);
2) reacting polyethylene glycol with 4,4'-dimethoxytrityl chloride to form 2-[bis-(4-dimethoxytrityl)-poly(ethylene glycol)];
3) reacting the compound formed in the step 2) and a compound of the following chemical formula 1 to form a compound of the following structural formula I;
4) reacting the formed compound of the following structural formula I and 4-nitrophenylchloroformate to form a compound of the following structural formula II;
5) reacting the compound of the following structural formula I formed in the step 3) and N-succinimidyl trifluoroacetic acid to form a compound of the following structural formula III; and
6) reacting the LCAA-CPG compound formed in the step 1) with the compounds of the following structural formulas I, II, and III respectively formed in the steps 3) to 5), respectively.
[where, R is alkyl, alkenyl, alkynyl, aryl, arylalkyl, heteroalkyl, or heteroaryl; and n is an integer of no less than 5 and no more than 120].

Moreover, the present invention provides a method for preparing 3'-PEG-CPG of the following structural formula IV, the method including:
1) reacting CPG with 3-aminopropyltriethoxysilane to form LCAA-CPG;
2) reacting polyethylene glycol with 4,4'-dimethoxytrityl chloride to form 2-[bis-(4-dimethoxytrityl)-poly(ethylene glycol)];
3) reacting the compound formed in the step 2) and a compound of the following formula 1 to form a compound of the following structural formula I;
4) reacting the formed compound of the following structural formula I and 4-nitrophenylchloroformate to form a compound of the following structural formula II;
5) reacting the compound of the following structural formula I formed in the step 3) and N-succinimidyl trifluoroacetic acid to form a compound of the following structural formula III; and
6) reacting the LCAA-CPG compound formed in the step 1) with the compounds of the following structural formulas I, II, and III respectively formed in the steps 3) to 5), respectively.
[where, R is alkyl, alkenyl, alkynyl, aryl, arylalkyl, heteroalkyl, or heteroaryl; and n is an integer of no less than 5 and no more than 120].

3'-PEG-CPG preparation sequence;

sense 5'-AAGGAGAUCAACAUUUUCA(dTdT)-PEG(6664.96Da + 2000Da) (Sequence ID No. 1)

antisense 5'-UGAAAAUGUUGAUCUCCUU(dTdT)-PEG(6592.84Da + 2000Da) (Sequence ID No. 5)

3'-PEG-CPG preparation sequence;

sense 5'-AAGGAGAUCAACAUUUUCA(dTdT)-PEG(6664.96Da + 2000Da) (Sequence ID No. 1)

antisense 5'-UGAAAAUGUUGAUCUCCUU(dTdT)-PEG(6592.84Da + 2000Da) (Sequence ID No. 5)

claim.claim-text:
A method for preparing 3'-PEG-CPG of the following structural formula IV, the method comprising:
1) reacting CPG with 3-aminopropyltriethoxysilane to form long chain alkyl amine controlled pore glass (LCAA-CPG);
2) reacting polyethylene glycol with 4,4'-dimethoxytrityl chloride to form 2-[bis-(4-dimethoxytrityl)-poly(ethylene glycol)];
3) reacting the compound formed in the step 2) with a compound of the following formula 1 to form a compound of the following structural formula I;
4) reacting the formed compound of the following structural formula I with 4-nitrophenylchloroformate to form a compound of the following structural formula II;
5) reacting the compound of the following structural formula I formed in the step 3) with N-succinimidyl trifluoroacetic acid to form a compound of the following structural formula III; and
6) reacting the LCAA-CPG compound formed in the step 1) with the compounds of the following structural formulas I, II, or III respectively formed in the steps 3) to 5), respectively.





wherein, R is alkyl, alkenyl, alkynyl, aryl, arylalkyl, heteroalkyl, or heteroaryl; and n is an integer of no less than 5 and no more than 120.
